content:
This feels clash-like.
Trying it out, but if it's less than 3 lines of code I'm going to root for clash.

I have the right buildings but I have a problem with  the end of lines.
In French:

Échec
Trouvé :
Rien
Attendu :
Rien

Hi Konrad_Wer,

your output description is a bit confusing. The formulation:
"Pictures of a highest buildings" can be understood as one should should pring any one tall building. However the output you provide show ALL the tall buildings of the city. Moreover, those seem to be in a specific order. 
Could you please rework your outputs and/or output description for it to be consistent?

Thanks
I have improved the output description.
I have checked that and I think that you are printing empty line after the last building, whereas you should print them only between the pictures of buildings.

Ok, it doesn't end up 3 lines, but the spirit is there.

(specifically, it's less than 3 lines (and a single expression, no variables) to solve the core of the problem, the rest is various specific idiosyncrasies: trim spaces on the right, account for various amounts of free space above, account for fencepost stuff (leading blanks, spacing between buildings, trailing blanks)
(that and imports)

So I'm torn. It's a bit much for a clash (based on memory), but for all the wrong reasons.

Well it depends on the appraoch you have for your code. If you don't know tricks, this can get pretty big. (My solution: creating a building class inheriting from IComparable. Parsing the input and creating a new instance of building for each of them with their index, their heigths and their graphical representation trimmed. Filling of all them in a List<Building> , sorting the list and printing the highests one by order of index. this takes more than 3 lines :p )

Sounds complex enough. :-P

I just went: transpose; count heights; isolate buildings; sort and keep best; transpose back.

http://pastebin.com/9pE0jYaP

All the accidental complexity is what I mentioned above.

Oh well, who am I to argue with the crowd if it's going to pass anyway and there's easy XP to make?

At least I fixed part of the text. Ha!
That’s what I think too but my code should not print an empty line after the last building.
